   Up Arrow to Map   1. Boundary Dam Boat Launch

        Waterbody: Boundary Lake
        Site Manager: Seattle City Light
        Nearest City: Metaline


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            30 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - closed during the winter months

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - reservoir levels may prohibit use of the boat ramp

        Driving Directions:

        From Metaline, N on SR 31 1 mi; L on Boundary Rd, go 10.2 mi; R at
        Boundary Dam sign, go 1 mi; R at campground/boat launch sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade with adequate traction. Boundary
        Dam Park also offers campsites, lawn areas, restrooms, and
        historical landmarks.


   Up Arrow to Map   2. Metaline Waterfront Park

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Metaline City of
        Nearest City: Metaline


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the river will periodically ice up during the winter.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may become too high or too low to effectively
        use the ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        N on SR 31 in Metaline, turn R just before crossing Lton Creek.
        Follow Rd 200 ft. past entrance sign to Metaline Waterfront Park.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and is located on a section of
        the river with a slow current. The right side of the ramp has an
        abrupt edge and is developing undermining erosion. No designated
        disabled parking. Metaline Waterfront Park also has several picnic
        shelters, a lawn area, play equipment, softball field, and restroom
        facilities.


   Up Arrow to Map   3. East Sullivan Lake Campgrond

        Waterbody: Sullivan Lake
        Site Manager: USFS CNF Sullivan Lake RD
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            16 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - The lake freezes over during the winter. The boat ramp is open
        as long as the lake is ice free and the access to the ramp is snow
        free. The campground, however, is closed in September.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Metaline Falls, N on SR 31, 1 mi; R on Sullivan Lake Rd, go 5.5
        mi; L on FR 22, go .25 mi; R at Sullivan Lake Campground.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade. V-groove surfacing
        also enhances vehicle traction. No designated disabled parking. No
        bull-rails on loading float. Sullivan Lake Campground also offers
        tent campsites, picnic area, hiking trails, R.V. campsites, group
        campsites, vault toilets, swimming area, and a R.V. dump station.


   Up Arrow to Map   4. Campbell Park

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Pend Oreille PUD
        Nearest City: Ione


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may become to high or low to effectively use
        the boat launch.

        Driving Directions:

        From Ione, N on SR 31 3.5 mi; R at Box Canyon Dam; L at Project
        Office, gravel Rd becomes boat ramp.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is long with a moderate grade and is located on a
        section of river with a slow/ moderate current. No designated
        disabled parking. Day-use visitors could park in the Visitors
        Center/ Project Office parking lot. Campbell Park also offers
        campsites, a swimming area, picnic area, and vault toilet.


   Up Arrow to Map   5. Noisy Creek Campground

        Waterbody: Sullivan Lake
        Site Manager: USFS CNF Sullivan Lake RD
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     8 Paved Spaces, No Striping

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  None

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the campground is closed around mid- October, but the boat
        ramp is open as long as the lake is free of ice and the roads into
        the area are snow free.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From SR 31 south of Ione, E on Sullivan Lake Rd 8 mi to campground.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade with adequate traction.
        Both sides of the ramp have abrupt edges and show impacts from
        undermining erosion. No designated disabled parking. Day-use parking
        is between the hours of 6 A.M. and 10 P.M. daily. Noisy Creek
        Campground also offers vault toilets, campsites, a swimming area,
        and hiking trails.


   Up Arrow to Map   6. Big Meadow Lake Campground

        Waterbody: Big Meadow Lake
        Site Manager: USFS CNF Colville RD
        Nearest City: Colville


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            8 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the campground is open as long as the campgound is accessible
        by vehicles. Amenities may be locked in the winter.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Colville, E on SR 20 1 mi; L on Aladdin Rd, go 1.8 mi; R on FR
        47.2, go 16.5 mi; R on FR 2695, go 4.5 mi; R at Big Meadow Lake
        Campground.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade. The gravel in between the
        concrete planks is beginning to wash away. No designated disabled
        parking. Big Meadow Campground also offers campsites, vault toilets,
        accessible fishing dock, accessible trail, and a wildlife viewing
        tower. Moose are sometimes seen in the meadows around the lake.


   Up Arrow to Map   7. Edgewater Campground

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: USFS CNF Sullivan Lake RD
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            1 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the campground is closed from September to mid to late May.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the reservoir level may drop below the boat ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From SR 31 S of Ione, E on Sullivan Lake Rd .5 mi; cross Pend
        Oreille River, turn L on Box Canyon Rd, go 2 mi; L at Edgewater
        Campground.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and is located on a section of
        the river with a slow current. Some of the concrete planks have
        slipped out of position. The edges to the ramp are protected by
        rocks to prevent erosion. Edgewater Campground also offers a picnic
        area and campsites. The day-use areas are open from 7:00 A.M. to
        10:00 P.M.


   Up Arrow to Map   8. Ione Park & Swim Pool

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Ione Parks & Rec Dept
        Nearest City: Ione


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Loading Float
                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            25 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may become too high to effectively use the
        ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        In Ione at milepost 4 on SR 31, E 2 blocks to Ione Park.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade. The gravel from between the
        planks is beginning to wash out. There is an abrupt edge on the
        upper section of the ramp. No designated disabled parking. Ione Park
        also has lawn areas, play equipment, picnic tables, flush restrooms,
        and a swimming pool.


   Up Arrow to Map   9. Leo Lake Campground

