   Up Arrow to Map   10. Blueslide Resort

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Blueslide Resort
        Nearest City: Spokane


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            16 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - generally, April through October

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - river level may become too high during certain times of the
        year to effectively launch.

        Driving Directions:

        From Spokane, N on US 2, 30 mi; L on SR 211, go 16 mi; L on SR 20,
        go 18.5 mi; R at Blueslide Resort.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is long and has a moderate to steep grade. A fee is
        charged for day-use visitors ($5.00/ round trip, $7.00/ resort staff
        launching or loading boat). No fee is charged for overnight guests
        of the resort. No designated disabled parking. Blueslide Resort also
        offers boat moorage, R.V. campsites with full hook-ups, flush
        restroom, showers, laundry facility, rental cabins, tent campsites,
        store, lawn area, play equipment, motel rooms, meeting hall,
        swimming pool, public phone, and picnic area.


   Up Arrow to Map   11. Old Ruby Ferry East

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Pend Oreille County of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            3 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may become too high to effectively use the
        access site.

        Driving Directions:

        From SR 31 just S of Ione, E on Sullivan Lake Rd .5 mi; crossing
        Pend Oreille River, R on LeClerc Rd, go 15 mi; R on unmarked gravel
        Rd, go 200 ft. to boat ramp.
        Site Description:

        The river access ramp has a gentle grade with a sand and rock
        surface. The ramp is also located on a section of the river that has
        a fairly slow current. A heavy boat may be difficult to pull out due
        to the loose sand and rock surface. No designated disabled parking.
        No sign indicates this boat access. The site used to be a ferry
        landing in years past. No other amenity exists at this site besides
        the access ramp and limited parking. The remnant structure of the
        ferry landing presents an underwater obstacle, but trailerable boats
        could launch and load on either side of this obstacle.


   Up Arrow to Map   12. Ruby Ferry (WDFW) - Pend Oreille River

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            15 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may become too high to use the ramp during
        certain times in the year.

        Driving Directions:

        From Spokane, N on US 2, 30 mi; L on SR 211, go 16 mi; L on SR 20,
        go 15 mi; R at "Public Fishing" sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate to steep grade and is located on a
        section of the river with a slow current. The left side of the ramp
        has an abrupt edge and is undermined. The gravel has washed away
        from between the planks exposing the steel fasteners. Some concrete
        planks are deteriorating to the point of exposing re-bar. No
        designated disabled parking. No overnight parking or camping.


   Up Arrow to Map   13. Panhandle Campground

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: USFS CNF Newport RD
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the boat ramp is open as long as the access road is snow free,
        but the campground is closed mid-September to mid-May.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may become too high or too low to effectively
        use the boat ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From SR 31 just S of Ione, E on Sullivan Lake Rd .5 mi; cross Pend
        Oreille River, R on LeClerc Rd, go 17.5 mi; R at Panhandle
        Campground sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and is located on a section of
        the river with a slow current. The ramp surfaces are uneven with the
        right lane severely undermined. Concrete planks are cracked and
        broken. Erosion has created abrupt edges and exposed steel
        fasteners. No designated disabled parking. The boat ramp is in the
        day-use area which is open from 6:00 A.M. to 10:00 P.M. Panhandle
        Campground also has campsites, vault toilets, changing stations,
        lawn areas, and river front beach access.


   Up Arrow to Map   14. Half Moon Lake

        Waterbody: Half Moon Lake
        Site Manager: USFS CNF Newport RD
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     1 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            2 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - snow will prevent vehicle access to the lake during the
        winter.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Usk, NE on Kings Lake Rd 6.2 mi; at 'Y' veer L on FR 5030, go
        1.8 mi; boat ramp on L side of Rd at N end of lake.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a very steep grade. At the shoreline the ramp then
        flattens out. Primarily, this is a good hand launch site.


   Up Arrow to Map   15. North Skookum Boat Ramp

        Waterbody: North Skookum Lake
        Site Manager: Natural Resources Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - open the end of April through October

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From SR 20 at Usk, E on Kings Lake Rd 8.4 mi; L at "Public Access"
        sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a steep grade and ruts developing from vehicles'
        spinning wheels. This boat ramp would be difficult to use with a
        vehicle without adequate ground clearance and 4 wheel drive. No
        designated disabled parking. No overnight parking or camping. Beyond
        the boat ramp and parking, no other amenity exists at this site.
        Several downed trees and tops are laying around the parking area.


   Up Arrow to Map   16. North Skookum Resort

        Waterbody: North Skookum Lake
        Site Manager: Natural Resources Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Loading Float
                            1 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            4 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - closed during the winter months.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From SR 20 at Usk, E on Kings Lake Rd 8.5 mi; L at campground.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade with a narrow approach. Primarily
        used as a hand launch type ramp, but it can handle trailerable
        boats. North Skookum Resort also offers campsites with water, flush
        restrooms, and showers. No designated disabled parking. A fee is
        charged to day-use only visitors to use the boat ramp [$1.00). There
        is no charge for registered guests of the resort.


   Up Arrow to Map   17. South Skookum Campground

        Waterbody: South Skookum Lake
        Site Manager: USFS CNF Newport RD
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            12 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - open the end of April through October.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From SR 20 at Usk, NE on Kings Lake Rd 8 mi; R on Kings Mountain Rd,
        go .5 mi; L to campground at second Rd.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade from the shoreline in, but a slight
        drop off at the upper ramp. No designated disabled parking. South
        Skookum Campground also offers campsites, vault toilets, and trail
        access. There is an overflow parking area at the west side of the
        campground.


   Up Arrow to Map   18. Town Park (Cusick)

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Cusick Town of
        Nearest City: Cusick


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   1 Concrete Ramp
                                   1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     14 Paved Spaces, No Striping

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   14 Paved Spaces, No Striping

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - site is not accessible when the Pend Oreille River is
        flooding.

        Driving Directions:

        N on SR 20 at Cusick, turn R at Calispell Creek, go .5 mi; L to
        Cusick Park.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate to steep grade. The ramp surface is
        60-degree V-groove to enhance traction. The loading float provides a
        large area for several boats to use at one time. Asphalt in the
        parking area is sinking in places. This site is prone to floods
        occasionally.


   Up Arrow to Map   19. Kalispel Riverside Park

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Kalispel Indian Tribe
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            30 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may become too low to effectively ue the boat
        ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From SR 20 in Usk, E on Kings Lake Rd 1 mi; L on LeClerc Rd, go 2.5
        mi; L at Kalispel Tribal Headquarters, go .75 mi; L to boat launch.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and is located on a section of
        river with a slow current. There is a significant drop off at the
        end of the ramp. No designated disabled parking. This site is
        located next to the Tribal Pow Wow grounds.


   Up Arrow to Map   20. Keo's Korner (Usk General Store)

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Usk General Store
        Nearest City: Usk


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            25 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the Pend Oreille River may be too high or too low to
        effectively use the boat ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        On SR 20 at Usk, E on Kings Lake Rd .5 mi; past Usk General Store,
        turn L; follow gravel Rd to ramp at bottom of hill.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a steep grade and an uneven surface. The ramp is
        protected from the river current (except during floods) by a channel
        and basin. When the water level is low, launching can occur at the
        river bank. No designated disabled parking. This site also offers
        primitive campsites. Sani-cans are nearby at the Usk General Store.
        A fee is charged to use the boat ramp ($1.00).


   Up Arrow to Map   21. Pondoray Shores Boat Launch

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Pend Oreille County of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            3 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the river will periodically freeze over during the winter.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may become too high or too low to effectively
        use the launch.

        Driving Directions:

        From Newport, E on US 2 .5 mi; cross Pend Oreille River, turn L on
        LeCerc Rd, go 11 mi; L on Pondoray Shores Rd; go .7 mi; at 90 degree
        L, continue straight to ramp.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a steep grade and a loose gravel base. Ruts are
        developing due to vehicles spinning their wheels. Large rocks are on
        the surface at the shoreline and below. No designated disabled
        parking. No other amenities exist except for the boat access and
        limited parking. No sign indicates the location of this site. The
        gravel roadway to the ramp is rough and somewhat overgrown.


   Up Arrow to Map   22. Greggs Road Boat Launch

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Pend Oreille County of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            3 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river levels may become too high or too low to effectively
        use the boat ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From Newport, E on US 2, .5 mi; cross Pend Oreille River, turn L on
        LeClerc Rd, go 9 mi; L on Greggs Rd, go .75 mi; L on unmarked paved
        Rd, go 200 ft. to ramp.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a steep grade and is located on a section of the
        river with a slow current. Abrupt edges have developed on both sides
        of the ramp. No designated disabled parking. No directional sign to
        indicate the location of the boat ramp. No other amenities exist at
        this site besides the boat ramp and limited parking. Gravel has been
        placed at the end of the boat ramp to serve as an extension of the
        boat ramp.


   Up Arrow to Map   23. Sandy Shores Boat Ramp

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: Pend Oreille County of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            3 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may be too high or too low to effectively use
        the boat ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From Newport, E on US 2, .5 mi; cross Pend Oreille River, L on
        LeClerc Creek Rd, go 4.5 mi; L on Sandy Shores Rd,go .2 mi; R at
        'T'; go to Rd end.
        Site Description:

        The ramp has a moderate grade. The sides and end of the ramp have
        abrupt edges and show the effects of undermining erosion. The
        approach to the ramp has several potholes in the asphalt. No
        designated disabled parking. Beyond the boat ramp and limited
        parking, no other amenity exists at this site. The boat ramp grade
        flattens out from the shoreline into the water.


   Up Arrow to Map   24. Marshall Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Marshall Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            3 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            25 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the site is open from the end of April through October.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Newport, E on US 2, .7 mi; L on Le Clerc Creek Rd 2.2 mi; veer
        R on Bead Lake Rd, go 2.5 mi; veer R on Marshall Lake Rd, go 1.2 mi;
        L at "Public Fishing" sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade. Traction may be hindered by the
        loose gravel surface. No designated disabled parking. The access
        site is located between two resorts which offer camping, boat
        rentals, a store, and fuel. The posted maximum speed on Marshall
        Lake is 5 miles per hour. Swimming is prohibited. Accessibility from
        the parking area to the water would be difficult due to the
        topography between the two areas.


   Up Arrow to Map   25. Pioneer Park (Pend Oreille Co.)

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: USFS CNF Newport RD
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     8 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            8 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - The boat ramp is open as long as the roads to the ramp are
        snow free. The campground is closed mid-September to mid/ late May.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may be too high or too low to effectively use
        the boat ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From Newport, E on US 2 .7 mi to Idaho; cross Pend Oreille River,
        turn L on Le Clerc Rd, go 2 mi; L at Pioneer Park.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a steep grade and an uneven surface. The steel
        fasteners are exposed and moderately corroded. The left side of the
        ramp has an abrupt edge and is developing undermining erosion. The
        boat ramp area is a day-use site only. Pioneer Park also offers a
        picnic area, R.V. campsites, and tent campsites. The Boat launch
        Overflow Parking area provides an additional 7 spaces and 1
        designated disabled parking space.


   Up Arrow to Map   26. Old American Kampground

        Waterbody: Pend Oreille River
        Site Manager: K/M Resorts of America
        Nearest City: Newport


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the boat ramp is only available for public use during the
        slower season for the campground. Generally, after Labor Day.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the river level may become too high or too low to effectively
        launch/ load a boat.

        Driving Directions:

        In Newport on US 2, N on Newport Ave (across from Safeway) .25 mi to
        entrance of R.V. park.
        Site Description:

        A fee is charged to use the boat ramp. Parking can be found up the
        hill from the boat ramp near the campground office. The Old American
        Kampground also offers R.V. campsites with hook-ups, restrooms with
        showers, and laundry facilities. The Old American Kampground is a
        membership only campground, but does allow public visitors to camp
        for attending membership sales meeting.


   Up Arrow to Map   27. Davis Lake (WDFW) - Pend Oreille Co.

        Waterbody: Davis Lake (Pend Oreille Co.)
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Gravel Ramp
                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            20 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the lake will freeze over during the winter.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Spokane, N on US 2, 30 mi; L on SR 211, go 10 mi; L just before
        Davis Lake Rd to enter launch area.
        Site Description:

        The concrete plank boat ramp has a moderate grade. The steel
        fasteners are exposed with moderate corrosion. A few fasteners are
        also broken. Several sections of the ramp have shifted positions and
        have become unevenly spaced. The ramp surface is uneven The planks
        at the shoreline have become undermined by wave erosion. No
        designated disabled parking. No overnight parking or camping. The
        posted speed limit on Davis Lake is 5 miles per hour.


   Up Arrow to Map   28. Sacheen Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Sacheen Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            60 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - open the end of April throgh October.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Spokane, N on US 2, 30 mi; L on SR 211; go 4 mi; L on Sacheen
        Terrace Rd, go .25 mi; L at "Public Fishing" sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade and an uneven surface. There are
        abrupt edges on the sides and front of the ramp. Steel fasteners are
        exposed and developing rust. No designated disabled parking. No
        overnight parking or camping within the parking area. The parking
        lot has a significant slope, however, accessibility may be easier at
        the lower end. The posted speed limit on Sacheen Lake is 35 miles
        per hour. The vault toilets are "round" fiberglass units with broken
        vent pipes.


   Up Arrow to Map   29. Diamond Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Diamond Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Paved Spaces, No Striping

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   35 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - open the end of April through October.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Spokane, N on US 2, 34 mi; L on Green Rd, go 1 block; R on S
        Shore Rd, immediate L to follow paved Rd 200 ft. to launch area.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade. Steel fasteners are
        exposed with a few fasteners missing bolts. Concrete planks are
        undermined at the shoreline. No designated disabled parking. No
        overnight parking or camping within the parking area. The parking
        area near the boat ramp is mostly paved with paths connecting the
        vault toilets. The posted maximum speed limit on the lake is 35
        miles per hour. A majority of the vehicle/ trailer parking is across
        South Shore Road from the access area.


   Up Arrow to Map   30. Horseshoe Lake - Pend Oreille (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Horseshoe Lake (Pend Oreille Co.)
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            25 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - open the end of April through October.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Deer Park, N on Short Rd 6 mi; R (east) on Davis Rd, go 1 mi; L
        on Sherman Rd, go 2.5 mi; L on Horseshoe Lake Rd, go 4 mi; R at
        "Public Fishing" sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and an even surface. No
        designated disabled parking. No overnight parking or camping. The
        parking lot surface is large gravel that makes accessibility
        difficult. Westbrook Resort, which rents boats and cabins and also
        has a convenience store, is located next to the access site. A
        neighbor mentioned that swimmers will sometimes impede boaters
        wishing to launch or load. Swimmers in the area will also migrate
        over to nearby private property and "take over" a dock. The posted
        speed limit on Horseshoe Lake is 5 miles per hour. The vault toilet
        is a 'round' fiberglass unit.



